---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"Private Tabs That Stay Out of Your History | Blanc Browser"}
  description={"Open a Blanc private tab to keep pages out of browsing history, session restore, and reopen-closed—then close the private tab when you are done."}
  path="/features/private-tabs"
  page="feature-private-tabs"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"Keep private pages out of Blanc history, session restore, and reopen-closed."}
  ogImage="/feature-private-tabs.png"
  ogImageAlt={"Blanc private-tab state with a dark page, dashed Island outline, and private close chip."}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Features","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Private tabs","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features/private-tabs"}]}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-detail-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/features">features</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">private tabs</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--detail feature-hero--text" aria-labelledby="private-title"><p class="section-kicker">a clean trail</p><h1 id="private-title">Private tabs that stay out of the record.</h1><p>Pages opened in a private tab are not written to Blanc history and are not restored when you reopen the browser.</p></section>
  <figure class="product-capture feature-capture">
    <div class="demo-stage island-figure" data-theme="private" role="img" aria-label="A Blanc private tab: the Island has a dashed outline and hollow tab dots with a 'private' quick-exit chip, floating over Blanc's dark private page.">
      <div class="demo-page" aria-hidden="true"><div class="bar w1"></div><div class="bar w2"></div><div class="bar w3"></div><div class="bar w4"></div></div>
      <div class="demo-island private" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="pill">
          <div class="dots"><span></span><span class="cur"></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="priv-chip">private <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M3 3 L9 9 M9 3 L3 9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figcaption>A private tab visibly changes the Island, and its quick-exit chip closes the tab when you are done.</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section class="feature-copy-grid feature-copy-grid--top" aria-labelledby="private-behavior-title">
    <div><p class="section-kicker">what stays private</p><h2 id="private-behavior-title">Use a private tab, then leave no Blanc trail behind.</h2></div>
    <div class="feature-copy-list">
      <article><h3>Not in history.</h3><p>Pages you visit in a private tab stay out of Blanc's browsing history, so they do not become part of the local record.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Not waiting after a restart.</h3><p>Private tabs are excluded from session restore and reopen-closed. They do not quietly return the next time you open Blanc.</p></article>
      <article><h3>One simple exit.</h3><p>The private chip on the Island is a quick way to close the active private tab when you are finished.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <aside class="truth-note" aria-labelledby="private-note-title"><p class="section-kicker">good to know</p><h2 id="private-note-title">Private does not mean anonymous.</h2><p>Private tabs share one separate in-memory browsing session with other private tabs opened during the same Blanc run; they do not share cookies or site storage with regular tabs, and the private session is discarded when Blanc quits. Websites, downloads, your network, or an employer may still observe activity, and files you explicitly save remain on disk.</p><a class="text-link" href="/privacy#what-stays-on-your-device" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="private-tabs" data-cta-position="truth-note">Read the full privacy policy <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></aside>
  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="private-close-title"><p class="section-kicker">ready when you need it</p><h2 id="private-close-title">Keep a private page out of the record.</h2><a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="private-tabs" data-cta-position="feature-close">download blanc</a></section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
